[<p>Network executives said the series is meant to provide context\xa0to the attention surrounding the debate in America over excessive force\xa0and policing.</p>, <p>\u201cEvery day the demands for more transparency in law enforcement continues to come from both civilians and police across the country,\u201d <a href="/web/20161004171358/http://www.aenetworks.com/article/ae-announces-new-weekly-event-series-live-pd" target="_blank">said Rob Sharenow</a>, executive vice president and general manger of A&amp;E and Lifetime. \u201c<em>Live PD\xa0</em>will not only highlight the difficult work being done by our men and women in uniform as they go out into the streets never knowing what to expect, but also answers citizens\u2019 calls for clarity.\u201d</p>, <p>Former news executive producer at CNN, ABC, and NBC, David Doss, takes the helm\xa0as show runner for the series.</p>, <p><em>\u201cLive PD</em>\xa0will go beyond the linear experience,\u201d an A&amp;E Networks <a href="/web/20161004171358/http://www.aenetworks.com/article/ae-announces-new-weekly-event-series-live-pd" target="_blank">release said</a> Monday. \u201cA live social media component will take audiences behind the scenes of the <em>Live PD</em>\xa0studio to pull back the curtain of the groundbreaking series.\u201d</p>, <p>Journalist Dan Abrams, ABC\u2019s\xa0chief legal affairs anchor and a\xa020-year veteran news journalist,\xa0will host <em>Live PD\xa0</em>from inside the\xa0studio alongside Dallas Police Department detectives Rich Emberlin and Kevin Jackson. Detectives Jackson and Emberlin, expert law enforcement officers with decades of experience \u2014 having served\xa0together in Patrol, SWAT and Criminal Intelligence for the Dallas Police Department \u2014 will offer live commentary for the show.</p>, <p><em>Live PD\xa0</em>will\xa0premiere Friday, October 28 at 9 PM and will be presented in\xa0eight two-hour\xa0episodes.</p>, <p>\xa0</p>, <p><em>Follow Jerome Hudson on Twitter:\xa0<a href="/web/20161004171358/https://twitter.com/JeromeEHudson" target="_blank">@JeromeEHudson</a></em></p>]